[
  {
    "id": "kp-9.1-01",
    "section": "9.1",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Types of Data",
    "title_zh": "数据类型",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "Data can be classified into different types based on what they represent and how they are measured.\n\n**Qualitative data** (Categorical) describes qualities or characteristics that are not numerical, such as colors, car brands, or names.\n\n**Quantitative data** (Numerical) represents quantities and can be further divided into two types:\n\n**Discrete data** can only take specific, isolated values, often as a result of counting. Examples include the number of children in a family ($0, 1, 2, \\ldots$) or shoe sizes ($6, 6.5, 7, \\ldots$).\n\n**Continuous data** can take any value within a range, often as a result of measuring. Examples include height ($165.4$ cm), weight ($52.18$ kg), or time ($12.5$ seconds).",
      "zh": "数据可以根据其代表的内容和测量方式进行分类。\n\n**定性数据**（分类数据）描述的是非数值的性质或特征，例如颜色、汽车品牌或姓名。\n\n**定量数据**（数值数据）代表数量，可以进一步分为两种类型：\n\n**离散数据** 只能取特定的、孤立的值，通常是计数的结果。例如家庭中孩子的数量（$0, 1, 2, \\ldots$）或鞋码（$6, 6.5, 7, \\ldots$）。\n\n**连续数据** 可以在某个范围内取任何值，通常是测量的结果。例如身高（$165.4$ cm）、体重（$52.18$ kg）或时间（$12.5$ 秒）。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-classify-data",
        "label": "Classify data as discrete or continuous",
        "label_zh": "将数据分类为离散或连续",
        "description": "Identify whether a given set of data (like time, number of people, or length) is discrete or continuous.",
        "description_zh": "辨别给定的一组数据（如时间、人数或长度）是离散的还是连续的。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-classify-data",
        "question": "State whether each of the following is discrete or continuous:\n(a) The number of goals scored in a football match.\n(b) The mass of an apple.\n(c) The temperature in a classroom.",
        "question_zh": "说明下列各项是离散数据还是连续数据：\n(a) 足球比赛中的进球数。\n(b) 一个苹果的质量。\n(c) 教室里的温度。",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** Analyze (a). Goals are counted ($0, 1, 2, \\ldots$). You cannot have $1.5$ goals. So, it is **discrete**. ✓\n\n**Step 2:** Analyze (b). Mass is measured and can take any value like $150.2$ g or $150.25$ g. So, it is **continuous**. ✓\n\n**Step 3:** Analyze (c). Temperature is measured on a scale and can take any value. So, it is **continuous**. ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 分析 (a)。进球数是通过计数的（$0, 1, 2, \\ldots$），不可能有 $1.5$ 个进球。因此它是**离散的**。✓\n\n**步骤2：** 分析 (b)。质量是通过测量的，可以取任何值，如 $150.2$ 克或 $150.25$ 克。因此它是**连续的**。✓\n\n**步骤3：** 分析 (c)。温度是在刻度上测量的，可以取任何值。因此它是**连续的**。✓",
        "source": "Adapted from 0580/21/M/J/20"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "Which of the following is an example of discrete data?",
        "q_zh": "下列哪项是离散数据的例子？",
        "o": [
          "The height of a tree",
          "The time taken to run 100m",
          "The number of books on a shelf",
          "The capacity of a water bottle"
"
        ],
        "a": 2,
        "e": "The number of books must be a whole number (you count them), so it is discrete. Height, time, and capacity are all measured and are continuous.",
        "e_zh": "书的数量必须是整数（通过计数得到），所以它是离散的。身高、时间和容量都是通过测量得到的，属于连续数据。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "discrete-data",
      "continuous-data"
    ],
    "tier": "both"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-9.1-02",
    "section": "9.1",
    "order": 2,
    "title": "Frequency Tables",
    "title_zh": "频数表",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "A frequency table is used to organize data by showing how many times each value or range of values occurs.\n\n**Tally marks** are often used to record data as it is collected. Four vertical lines with a diagonal fifth line represent a group of five (e.g., ||||).\n\n**Frequency** ($f$) is the total count of tally marks for a particular category.\n\n**Grouped frequency tables** are used for large sets of data or continuous data. Data is placed into intervals called **classes** (e.g., $0 < x \\leq 10$). Intervals should not overlap.",
      "zh": "频数表用于组织数据，显示每个值或数值范围出现的次数。\n\n**计数符号**（Tally）通常用于在收集数据时进行记录。四条垂直线加一条对角线代表一组五个（例如 ||||）。\n\n**频数** ($f$) 是特定类别计数符号的总数。\n\n**分组频数表** 用于处理大型数据集或连续数据。数据被放入称为**组别**（Classes）的区间中（例如 $0 < x \\leq 10$）。区间不应重叠。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-complete-table",
        "label": "Complete a frequency table from raw data",
        "label_zh": "根据原始数据完成频数表",
        "description": "Given a list of values, use tally marks to find the frequency of each category and complete the table.",
        "description_zh": "给定一组数值，使用计数符号找出每个类别的频数并完成表格。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-complete-table",
        "question": "The ages of 15 children are: $5, 7, 5, 6, 8, 7, 5, 9, 6, 7, 5, 8, 7, 6, 7$.\nComplete the frequency table for the age 7.\n\n| Age | Tally | Frequency |\n|---|---|---|\n| 7 | ? | ? |",
        "question_zh": "15个孩子的年龄分别是：$5, 7, 5, 6, 8, 7, 5, 9, 6, 7, 5, 8, 7, 6, 7$。\n完成年龄为 7 的频数表。\n\n| 年龄 | 计数 | 频数 |\n|---|---|---|\n| 7 | ? | ? |",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** Count how many times the number '7' appears in the list.\nThe list contains: $5, \\mathbf{7}, 5, 6, 8, \\mathbf{7}, 5, 9, 6, \\mathbf{7}, 5, 8, \\mathbf{7}, 6, \\mathbf{7}$.\nThere are 5 occurrences.\n\n**Step 2:** Write the tally marks for 5: ||||\n\n**Step 3:** Write the frequency as 5. ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 数一下列表中数字 '7' 出现了多少次。\n列表包含：$5, \\mathbf{7}, 5, 6, 8, \\mathbf{7}, 5, 9, 6, \\mathbf{7}, 5, 8, \\mathbf{7}, 6, \\mathbf{7}$。\n共出现了 5 次。\n\n**步骤2：** 写出 5 的计数符号：||||\n\n**步骤3：** 写出频数为 5。✓",
        "source": "Adapted from 0580/12/O/N/19"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "In a grouped frequency table, what does the class $10 < h \\leq 20$ represent?",
        "q_zh": "在分组频数表中，组别 $10 < h \\leq 20$ 代表什么？",
        "o": [
          "Heights from 10 to 20 including both",
          "Heights greater than 10 up to and including 20",
          "Heights from 10 up to but not including 20",
          "Heights exactly 10 or exactly 20"
        ],
        "a": 1,
        "e": "The symbol '<' means 'greater than' and '$\\leq$' means 'less than or equal to'. So it includes 20 but not 10.",
        "e_zh": "符号 '<' 表示 '大于'，'$\\leq$' 表示 '小于或等于'。因此它包含 20 但不包含 10。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "frequency",
      "tally"
    ],
    "tier": "both"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-9.3-01",
    "section": "9.3",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Mean, Median, Mode and Range",
    "title_zh": "平均数、中位数、众数和极差",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "These measures summarize a data set by describing its center and spread.\n\n**Mean** is the arithmetic average. Calculated by: $\\text{Mean} = \\frac{\\sum x}{n}$ (sum of all values divided by the number of values).\n\n**Median** is the middle value when data is arranged in order. If there are $n$ values, the position is $\\frac{n+1}{2}$. If $n$ is even, it's the mean of the two middle values.\n\n**Mode** is the value that occurs most frequently. A data set can have no mode, one mode, or be bimodal.\n\n**Range** is the difference between the highest and lowest values: $\\text{Range} = \\text{Highest} - \\text{Lowest}$. It measures the spread of the data.",
      "zh": "这些指标通过描述数据集的中心和离散程度来总结数据集。\n\n**平均数** (Mean) 是算术平均值。计算公式为：$\\text{Mean} = \\frac{\\sum x}{n}$（所有数值之和除以数值个数）。\n\n**中位数** (Median) 是数据按顺序排列时的中间值。如果有 $n$ 个数值，位置在 $\\frac{n+1}{2}$。如果 $n$ 是偶数，则是中间两个数的平均值。\n\n**众数** (Mode) 是出现频率最高的值。一个数据集可以没有众数、一个众数，或者是双峰的（有两个众数）。\n\n**极差** (Range) 是最大值与最小值之差：$\\text{极差} = \\text{最大值} - \\text{最小值}$。它衡量数据的离散程度。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-averages-list",
        "label": "Calculate averages from a list of numbers",
        "label_zh": "从数字列表计算统计量",
        "description": "Find the mean, median, mode, or range for a given small set of raw data.",
        "description_zh": "针对给出的一组小型原始数据，找出其平均数、中位数、众数或极差。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-averages-list",
        "question": "For the list of numbers: $2, 8, 5, 2, 3, 10, 4$, find:\n(a) the mode\n(b) the median\n(c) the mean",
        "question_zh": "对于数字列表：$2, 8, 5, 2, 3, 10, 4$，找出：\n(a) 众数\n(b) 中位数\n(c) 平均数",
        "solution": "**Step 1: Find the Mode.** The number $2$ appears twice, others appear once. Mode = $2$.\n\n**Step 2: Find the Median.** Arrange in order: $2, 2, 3, 4, 5, 8, 10$. There are 7 numbers. The middle one (4th) is $4$. Median = $4$.\n\n**Step 3: Find the Mean.** Sum = $2+8+5+2+3+10+4 = 34$. Mean = $34 \\div 7 \\approx 4.86$. ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：找众数。** 数字 $2$ 出现了两次，其他数字各出现一次。众数 = $2$。\n\n**步骤2：找中位数。** 按顺序排列：$2, 2, 3, 4, 5, 8, 10$。共有 7 个数字。中间的一个（第4个）是 $4$。中位数 = $4$。\n\n**步骤3：找平均数。** 总和 = $2+8+5+2+3+10+4 = 34$。平均数 = $34 \\div 7 \\approx 4.86$。✓",
        "source": "0580/22/M/J/18"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "What is the range of these temperatures: $-3^{\\circ}\\text{C}, 5^{\\circ}\\text{C}, 12^{\\circ}\\text{C}, -8^{\\circ}\\text{C}, 0^{\\circ}\\text{C}$?",
        "q_zh": "这些温度的极差是多少：$-3^{\\circ}\\text{C}, 5^{\\circ}\\text{C}, 12^{\\circ}\\text{C}, -8^{\\circ}\\text{C}, 0^{\\circ}\\text{C}$？",
        "o": [
          "$4^{\\circ}\\text{C}$",
          "$12^{\\circ}\\text{C}$",
          "$20^{\\circ}\\text{C}$",
          "$15^{\\circ}\\text{C}$"
        ],
        "a": 2,
        "e": "Range = Highest - Lowest = $12 - (-8) = 12 + 8 = 20$.",
        "e_zh": "极差 = 最大值 - 最小值 = $12 - (-8) = 12 + 8 = 20$。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "mean",
      "median",
      "mode",
      "range"
    ],
    "tier": "both"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-9.3-02",
    "section": "9.3",
    "order": 2,
    "title": "Averages from Frequency Tables",
    "title_zh": "频数表的平均数计算",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "When data is presented in a table, we use the frequencies to find averages.\n\n**Mean from discrete frequency table**: Sum up the product of each value ($x$) and its frequency ($f$), then divide by the total frequency: $\\text{Mean} = \\frac{\\sum f x}{\\sum f}$.\n\n**Estimated Mean from grouped data**: Since we don't know the exact values in a class, we use the **mid-interval value** ($m$) as an estimate: $\\text{Estimated Mean} = \\frac{\\sum f m}{\\sum f}$.\n\n**Modal Class**: The class interval with the highest frequency.",
      "zh": "当数据以表格形式呈现时，我们使用频数来计算平均指标。\n\n**离散频数表的平均数**：将每个数值 ($x$) 与其频数 ($f$) 的乘积相加，然后除以总频数：$\\text{Mean} = \\frac{\\sum f x}{\\sum f}$。\n\n**分组数据的估计平均数**：由于我们不知道组内数值的精确大小，我们使用**组中值** ($m$) 作为估计值：$\\text{估计平均数} = \\frac{\\sum f m}{\\sum f}$。\n\n**众数组** (Modal Class)：频数最高的组别区间。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-estimate-mean",
        "label": "Estimate the mean of grouped data",
        "label_zh": "估计分组数据的平均数",
        "description": "Use mid-interval values and frequencies to calculate an estimate for the mean of a continuous data set.",
        "description_zh": "利用组中值和频数计算连续数据集平均数的估计值。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-estimate-mean",
        "question": "The table shows the time, $t$ minutes, spent by students on homework.\n\n| Time ($t$) | Frequency ($f$) |\n|---|---|\n| $0 < t \\leq 20$ | 5 |\n| $20 < t \\leq 40$ | 8 |\n| $40 < t \\leq 60$ | 7 |\n\nCalculate an estimate for the mean time.",
        "question_zh": "下表显示了学生做作业的时间 $t$ 分钟。\n\n| 时间 ($t$) | 频数 ($f$) |\n|---|---|\n| $0 < t \\leq 20$ | 5 |\n| $20 < t \\leq 40$ | 8 |\n| $40 < t \\leq 60$ | 7 |\n\n计算平均时间的估计值。",
        "solution": "**Step 1: Find mid-values ($m$).** \nClasses: $(0+20)/2 = 10$; $(20+40)/2 = 30$; $(40+60)/2 = 50$.\n\n**Step 2: Calculate $f \\times m$.**\n$5 \\times 10 = 50$\n$8 \\times 30 = 240$\n$7 \\times 50 = 350$\n\n**Step 3: Sum them up.** $\\sum f m = 50 + 240 + 350 = 640$.\n\n**Step 4: Divide by total frequency.** $\\sum f = 5 + 8 + 7 = 20$.\nMean $\\approx 640 \\div 20 = 32$ minutes. ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：找到组中值 ($m$)。** \n各组：$(0+20)/2 = 10$；$(20+40)/2 = 30$；$(40+60)/2 = 50$。\n\n**步骤2：计算 $f \\times m$。**\n$5 \\times 10 = 50$\n$8 \\times 30 = 240$\n$7 \\times 50 = 350$\n\n**步骤3：求和。** $\\sum f m = 50 + 240 + 350 = 640$。\n\n**步骤4：除以总频数。** $\\sum f = 5 + 8 + 7 = 20$。\n平均数 $\\approx 640 \\div 20 = 32$ 分钟。✓",
        "source": "0580/41/M/J/21"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "Why is the mean from a grouped frequency table called an 'estimate'?",
        "q_zh": "为什么分组频数表的平均数被称为“估计值”？",
        "o": [
          "Because the math is usually wrong",
          "Because we don't know the exact values within each class interval",
          "Because the class intervals are too wide",
          "Because we use a calculator"
        ],
        "a": 1,
        "e": "We use the mid-value of each class because the original individual data points are lost in the grouping process, so we can't find the exact total.",
        "e_zh": "我们使用每组的组中值，是因为原始的单个数据点在分组过程中丢失了，所以我们无法算出准确的总和。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "modal-class",
      "mid-interval-value"
    ],
    "tier": "both"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-9.4-01",
    "section": "9.4",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Pie Charts and Bar Charts",
    "title_zh": "饼图与条形图",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "These diagrams are used to visually represent and compare categorical or discrete data.\n\n**Bar Charts** use the height (or length) of bars to represent frequency. Bars should be of equal width and usually have gaps between them for categorical data.\n\n**Pie Charts** use sectors of a circle to show proportions. The angle of each sector is proportional to the frequency: $\\text{Angle} = \\frac{\\text{Frequency}}{\\text{Total Frequency}} \\times 360^{\\circ}$.",
      "zh": "这些图表用于直观地表示和比较分类数据或离散数据。\n\n**条形图** 利用条形的高度（或长度）来表示频数。条形应宽度相等，分类数据之间通常留有间隙。\n\n**饼图** 利用圆形的扇区来显示比例。每个扇区的角度与频数成正比：$\\text{角度} = \\frac{\\text{频数}}{\\text{总频数}} \\times 360^{\\circ}$。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-pie-angle",
        "label": "Calculate angles for a pie chart",
        "label_zh": "计算饼图的角度",
        "description": "Convert frequencies into sector angles for drawing or interpreting a pie chart.",
        "description_zh": "将频数转换为扇区角度，以便绘制或解读饼图。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-pie-angle",
        "question": "A class of 30 students vote for their favorite color. 12 students chose Blue. Calculate the sector angle for Blue in a pie chart.",
        "question_zh": "一个有 30 名学生的班级投票选出最喜欢的颜色。12 名学生选择蓝色。计算饼图中蓝色的扇区角度。",
        "solution": "**Step 1: Identify frequency and total frequency.** Frequency = $12$, Total = $30$.\n\n**Step 2: Use the formula.** $\\text{Angle} = \\frac{12}{30} \\times 360^{\\circ}$.\n\n**Step 3: Calculate.** $\\frac{12}{30} = 0.4$. \n$0.4 \\times 360^{\\circ} = 144^{\\circ}$. ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：确定频数和总频数。** 频数 = $12$，总数 = $30$。\n\n**步骤2：使用公式。** $\\text{角度} = \\frac{12}{30} \\times 360^{\\circ}$。\n\n**步骤3：计算。** $\\frac{12}{30} = 0.4$。\n$0.4 \\times 360^{\\circ} = 144^{\\circ}$。✓",
        "source": "Adapted from 0580/22/F/M/17"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "If a pie chart sector has an angle of $90^{\\circ}$, what fraction of the total frequency does it represent?",
        "q_zh": "如果饼图的一个扇区角度为 $90^{\\circ}$，它占总频数的几分之几？",
        "o": [
          "$\\frac{1}{2}$",
          "$\\frac{1}{3}$",
          "$\\frac{1}{4}$",
          "$\\frac{1}{10}$"
        ],
        "a": 2,
        "e": "A full circle is $360^{\\circ}$. $\\frac{90}{360} = \\frac{1}{4}$.",
        "e_zh": "整个圆是 $360^{\\circ}$。$\\frac{90}{360} = \\frac{1}{4}$。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "pie-chart",
      "bar-chart"
    ],
    "tier": "both"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-9.4-02",
    "section": "9.4",
    "order": 2,
    "title": "Stem-and-Leaf Diagrams",
    "title_zh": "茎叶图",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "A stem-and-leaf diagram organizes data by dividing each number into a 'stem' (the leading digits) and a 'leaf' (the last digit).\n\n**Order**: Leaves must be arranged in ascending order on each row.\n\n**Key**: Every stem-and-leaf diagram MUST have a key to explain the values (e.g., $2 | 3$ means $23$).\n\nIt is useful for seeing the distribution of the data while keeping all original values.",
      "zh": "茎叶图通过将每个数字分为“茎”（前几位数字）和“叶”（最后一位数字）来组织数据。\n\n**顺序**：每一行中的叶子必须按升序排列。\n\n**图例** (Key)：每个茎叶图必须有一个图例来解释数值（例如，$2 | 3$ 表示 $23$）。\n\n茎叶图在保留所有原始数值的同时，能很好地展示数据的分布。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-read-stem",
        "label": "Extract information from a stem-and-leaf diagram",
        "label_zh": "从茎叶图中提取信息",
        "description": "Find the median, mode, or range from a given stem-and-leaf plot.",
        "description_zh": "从给定的茎叶图中找出中位数、众数或极差。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-read-stem",
        "question": "The diagram shows the heights of 10 plants:\n$1 | 2, 5, 8$\n$2 | 0, 3, 3, 7$\n$3 | 1, 4, 6$\nKey: $1 | 2 = 12$ cm\nFind the median height.",
        "question_zh": "图表显示了 10 株植物的高度：\n$1 | 2, 5, 8$\n$2 | 0, 3, 3, 7$\n$3 | 1, 4, 6$\n图例：$1 | 2 = 12$ 厘米\n找出中位数高度。",
        "solution": "**Step 1: Count total values.** $n = 10$.\n\n**Step 2: Find the middle positions.** Since 10 is even, we need the average of the 5th and 6th values.\n\n**Step 3: Locate values.** \n1st: 12, 2nd: 15, 3rd: 18, 4th: 20, **5th: 23**, **6th: 23**.\n\n**Step 4: Calculate median.** $(23 + 23) / 2 = 23$ cm. ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：统计总数。** $n = 10$。\n\n**步骤2：找到中间位置。** 因为 10 是偶数，我们需要第 5 个和第 6 个数值的平均数。\n\n**步骤3：确定数值。** \n第1个：12，第2个：15，第3个：18，第4个：20，**第5个：23**，**第6个：23**。\n\n**步骤4：计算中位数。** $(23 + 23) / 2 = 23$ 厘米。✓",
        "source": "Adapted from 0580/21/O/N/20"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
