  {
    "id": "kp-9.5-01",
    "section": "9.5",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Scatter Diagrams and Correlation",
    "title_zh": "散点图与相关性",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "A scatter diagram plots pairs of data to look for a relationship between two variables.\n\n**Correlation** describes the relationship. \n- **Positive correlation**: As one variable increases, the other also increases (points go 'up').\n- **Negative correlation**: As one variable increases, the other decreases (points go 'down').\n- **No correlation**: No clear pattern exists between the variables.\n\nCorrelation can be strong (points are close to a line) or weak (points are spread out).",
      "zh": "散点图通过绘制数据对来寻找两个变量之间的关系。\n\n**相关性** 用于描述这种关系：\n- **正相关**：随着一个变量增加，另一个变量也随之增加（点呈上升趋势）。\n- **负相关**：随着一个变量增加，另一个变量随之减少（点呈下降趋势）。\n- **无相关**：变量之间没有明显的规律。\n\n相关性可以是强的（点非常接近一条线）或弱的（点比较分散）。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-type-corr",
        "label": "Identify type of correlation",
        "label_zh": "识别相关性类型",
        "description": "Look at a scatter graph and describe the correlation (positive, negative, or none).",
        "description_zh": "观察散点图并描述其相关性（正相关、负相关或无相关）。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-type-corr",
        "question": "A student plots the age of a car against its price. What type of correlation would you expect?",
        "question_zh": "一名学生绘制了汽车车龄与价格的关系图。你预期会有哪种相关性？",
        "solution": "**Step 1: Think about the relationship.** Generally, as a car gets older (age increases), its value decreases.\n\n**Step 2: Conclusion.** One variable goes up while the other goes down. This is **negative correlation**. ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：思考两者关系。** 通常情况下，随着车龄增长（车龄增加），其价值会降低。\n\n**步骤2：结论。** 一个变量增加，另一个变量减少。这是**负相关**。✓",
        "source": "Adapted from 0580/23/M/J/19"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "If the points on a scatter diagram go from bottom-left to top-right, the correlation is:",
        "q_zh": "如果散点图上的点从左下方向右上方延伸，则该相关性为：",
        "o": [
          "Negative",
          "Zero",
          "Positive",
          "Vertical"
        ],
        "a": 2,
        "e": "Bottom-left to top-right means both variables increase together, which is positive correlation.",
        "e_zh": "从左下到右上意味着两个变量同时增加，即正相关。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "scatter-diagram",
      "correlation",
      "positive-correlation",
      "negative-correlation"
    ],
    "tier": "both"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-9.5-02",
    "section": "9.5",
    "order": 2,
    "title": "Line of Best Fit",
    "title_zh": "最佳拟合线",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "A **Line of Best Fit** is a straight line drawn through the center of the points on a scatter diagram to show the general trend.\n\nIt should have roughly an equal number of points above and below it. It does not need to pass through the origin or every point.\n\nIt is used for **Interpolation** (estimating a value within the data range) and **Extrapolation** (estimating a value outside the data range, which is less reliable).",
      "zh": "**最佳拟合线** 是在散点图上穿过点群中心的一条直线，用于显示总体趋势。\n\n线上方和下方的点数应大致相等。它不需要经过原点或每一个点。\n\n它用于**内插法**（估计数据范围内的值）和**外推法**（估计数据范围之外的值，后者不太可靠）。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-draw-estimate",
        "label": "Draw and use a line of best fit",
        "label_zh": "绘制并利用最佳拟合线",
        "description": "Draw the line and use it to estimate the value of one variable given the other.",
        "description_zh": "绘制直线，并在已知一个变量的情况下利用它估计另一个变量的值。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-draw-estimate",
        "question": "Given a scatter plot of height vs arm span, use your line of best fit to estimate the arm span of a person who is $170$ cm tall.",
        "question_zh": "已知身高与臂展的散点图，利用你的最佳拟合线估计一名身高 $170$ 厘米的人的臂展。",
        "solution": "**Step 1: Locate the value on the axis.** Find $170$ on the 'Height' axis.\n\n**Step 2: Go to the line.** Draw a vertical line from $170$ up to your Line of Best Fit.\n\n**Step 3: Read the answer.** Go horizontally from the line to the 'Arm Span' axis and read the value. (e.g., $168$ cm). ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：在轴上定位。** 在“身高”轴上找到 $170$。\n\n**步骤2：对应到直线。** 从 $170$ 向上画一条垂直线直到你的最佳拟合线。\n\n**步骤3：读取答案。** 从该点水平向“臂展”轴画线并读取数值（例如，$168$ 厘米）。✓",
        "source": "0580/42/M/J/20"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "Which of these is TRUE about a line of best fit?",
        "q_zh": "关于最佳拟合线，下列哪项是正确的？",
        "o": [
          "It must pass through $(0,0)$",
          "It must pass through every point",
          "It should follow the trend of the data points",
          "It can only be used for positive correlation"
        ],
        "a": 2,
        "e": "The line shows the trend. It doesn't have to start at $(0,0)$ and rarely passes through all points. It can be used for both positive and negative correlation.",
        "e_zh": "这条线反映了趋势。它不必从 $(0,0)$ 开始，也很少经过所有点。正相关和负相关都可以使用最佳拟合线。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "line-of-best-fit"
    ],
    "tier": "both"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-9.6-01",
    "section": "9.6",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Cumulative Frequency Curves",
    "title_zh": "累积频率曲线",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "Cumulative frequency is the 'running total' of frequencies.\n\nTo draw a **Cumulative Frequency Curve**:\n1. Create a cumulative frequency table by adding up frequencies as you go.\n2. Plot the cumulative frequency against the **upper class boundary** of each interval.\n3. Join the points with a smooth curve.\n\nThe curve always starts at $(L, 0)$, where $L$ is the lower boundary of the first class, and always goes upwards.",
      "zh": "累积频率是频数的“累计总和”。\n\n绘制**累积频率曲线**的步骤：\n1. 通过不断累加频数来创建累积频率表。\n2. 将累积频率对应每个组别的**上边界**（Upper boundary）进行描点。\n3. 用平滑的曲线连接各点。\n\n曲线总是从 $(L, 0)$ 开始（$L$ 是第一组的下边界），并且总是呈上升趋势。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-plot-cf",
        "label": "Plot a cumulative frequency curve",
        "label_zh": "绘制累积频率曲线",
        "description": "Complete a cumulative frequency table and use the values to plot the curve on a grid.",
        "description_zh": "完成累积频率表，并利用这些数值在坐标网格上绘制曲线。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-plot-cf",
        "question": "A table shows frequencies for mass ($m$): $0<m\\leq 10$ ($f=4$), $10<m\\leq 20$ ($f=10$). Write down the coordinates to plot for these two classes.",
        "question_zh": "表格显示了质量 ($m$) 的频数：$0<m\\leq 10$ ($f=4$)，$10<m\\leq 20$ ($f=10$)。写出这两组对应的描点坐标。",
        "solution": "**Step 1: Calculate cumulative frequency.** \nFirst point: $4$. \nSecond point: $4 + 10 = 14$.\n\n**Step 2: Use upper boundaries.** \nUpper boundaries are $10$ and $20$.\n\n**Step 3: Write coordinates.** \n$(10, 4)$ and $(20, 14)$. (Also start at $(0, 0)$). ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：计算累积频率。** \n第一个点：$4$。\n第二个点：$4 + 10 = 14$。\n\n**步骤2：使用上边界。** \n上边界分别为 $10$ 和 $20$。\n\n**步骤3：写出坐标。** \n$(10, 4)$ 和 $(20, 14)$。（通常也从 $(0, 0)$ 开始）。✓",
        "source": "0580/42/M/J/18"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "Cumulative frequency is plotted against which value?",
        "q_zh": "累积频率是对应哪个数值进行描点的？",
        "o": [
          "Lower class boundary",
          "Mid-interval value",
          "Upper class boundary",
          "The frequency"
        ],
        "a": 2,
        "e": "We plot against the upper boundary because the cumulative frequency represents the total number of items 'up to' that value.",
        "e_zh": "我们对应上边界描点，是因为累积频率代表了“直到”该数值为止的所有项目总数。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "cumulative-frequency"
    ],
    "tier": "extended"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-9.6-02",
    "section": "9.6",
    "order": 2,
    "title": "Quartiles and IQR",
    "title_zh": "四分位数与四分位距",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "From a cumulative frequency curve, we can estimate the median and quartiles.\n\n**Median** ($Q_2$) is the value at $50\\%$ of the total frequency ($n$).\n\n**Lower Quartile** ($Q_1$) is the value at $25\\%$ of the total frequency.\n\n**Upper Quartile** ($Q_3$) is the value at $75\\%$ of the total frequency.\n\n**Interquartile Range** (IQR) = $Q_3 - Q_1$. It measures the spread of the middle $50\\%$ of the data and is less affected by outliers than the range.",
      "zh": "从累积频率曲线中，我们可以估计中位数和四分位数。\n\n**中位数** ($Q_2$) 是总频数 ($n$) $50\\%$ 处对应的数值。\n\n**下四分位数** ($Q_1$) 是总频数 $25\\%$ 处对应的数值。\n\n**上四分位数** ($Q_3$) 是总频数 $75\\%$ 处对应的数值。\n\n**四分位距** (IQR) = $Q_3 - Q_1$。它衡量中间 $50\\%$ 数据的离散程度，比极差更不容易受异常值（离群点）的影响。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-read-cf-stats",
        "label": "Find median and IQR from a curve",
        "label_zh": "从曲线中寻找中位数和四分位距",
        "description": "Read the values on the x-axis corresponding to $0.25n, 0.5n,$ and $0.75n$ on the y-axis.",
        "description_zh": "读取 y 轴上 $0.25n, 0.5n$ 和 $0.75n$ 位置在 x 轴上对应的数值。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-read-cf-stats",
        "question": "For a total frequency of 80, the lower quartile is found at a cumulative frequency of 20, which corresponds to 15 kg on the x-axis. The upper quartile is found at 60, which corresponds to 42 kg. Find the IQR.",
        "question_zh": "总频数为 80，下四分位数在累积频率 20 处找到，对应 x 轴 15 千克；上四分位数在 60 处找到，对应 42 千克。求四分位距 (IQR)。",
        "solution": "**Step 1: Identify $Q_1$ and $Q_3$.** $Q_1 = 15$, $Q_3 = 42$.\n\n**Step 2: Use the formula.** $IQR = Q_3 - Q_1 = 42 - 15$.\n\n**Step 3: Calculate.** $IQR = 27$ kg. ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：确定 $Q_1$ 和 $Q_3$。** $Q_1 = 15$，$Q_3 = 42$。\n\n**步骤2：使用公式。** $IQR = Q_3 - Q_1 = 42 - 15$。\n\n**步骤3：计算。** $IQR = 27$ 千克。✓",
        "source": "0580/41/O/N/17"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "If $n=200$, what cumulative frequency do you use to find the upper quartile?",
        "q_zh": "如果 $n=200$，你使用哪个累积频率来寻找上四分位数？",
        "o": [
          "50",
          "100",
          "150",
          "175"
        ],
        "a": 2,
        "e": "Upper Quartile is at $75\\%$ of total. $0.75 \\times 200 = 150$.",
        "e_zh": "上四分位数位于总量的 $75\\%$ 处。$0.75 \\times 200 = 150$。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "lower-quartile",
      "upper-quartile",
      "interquartile-range"
    ],
    "tier": "extended"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-9.7-01",
    "section": "9.7",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Histograms",
    "title_zh": "直方图",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "Histograms are used to represent grouped continuous data, especially when class widths are unequal.\n\nIn a histogram, the **area** of the bar represents the frequency. \n\n**Frequency Density** is plotted on the vertical axis: $\\text{Frequency Density} = \\frac{\\text{Frequency}}{\\text{Class Width}}$.\n\nUnlike bar charts, there are no gaps between the bars.",
      "zh": "直方图用于表示分组连续数据，特别是当组距（组别宽度）不等时。\n\n在直方图中，条形的**面积**代表频数。\n\n**频数密度** (Frequency Density) 绘制在纵轴上：$\\text{频数密度} = \\frac{\\text{频数}}{\\text{组距}}$。\n\n与条形图不同，直方图的条形之间没有间隙。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-calc-fd",
        "label": "Calculate frequency density",
        "label_zh": "计算频数密度",
        "description": "Calculate the height of a bar for a histogram given the frequency and class interval.",
        "description_zh": "已知频数和组别区间，计算直方图条形的高度。"
      },
      {
        "id": "ep-complete-histogram",
        "label": "Complete a histogram",
        "label_zh": "完成直方图",
        "description": "Draw the bars of a histogram or find missing frequencies using the area of the bars.",
        "description_zh": "绘制直方图条形，或利用条形面积找出缺失的频数。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-calc-fd",
        "question": "A class interval is $10 < x \\leq 25$ and its frequency is $30$. Calculate the frequency density.",
        "question_zh": "组别区间为 $10 < x \\leq 25$，频数为 $30$。计算频数密度。",
        "solution": "**Step 1: Find the class width.** $25 - 10 = 15$.\n\n**Step 2: Use the formula.** $\\text{FD} = \\frac{\\text{Frequency}}{\\text{Width}} = \\frac{30}{15}$.\n\n**Step 3: Calculate.** $\\text{FD} = 2$. ✓",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：找到组距。** $25 - 10 = 15$。\n\n**步骤2：使用公式。** $\\text{FD} = \\frac{\\text{频数}}{\\text{组距}} = \\frac{30}{15}$。\n\n**步骤3：计算。** $\\text{FD} = 2$。✓",
        "source": "0580/42/O/N/19"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "What does the area of a bar in a histogram represent?",
        "q_zh": "直方图中条形的面积代表什么？",
        "o": [
          "Class Width",
          "Frequency Density",
          "Frequency",
          "Mean"
        ],
        "a": 2,
        "e": "By definition, $\\text{Area} = \\text{Width} \\times \\text{Height} = \\text{Width} \\times \\text{Frequency Density} = \\text{Frequency}$.",
        "e_zh": "根据定义，$\\text{面积} = \\text{宽度} \\times \\text{高度} = \\text{组距} \\times \\text{频数密度} = \\text{频数}$。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "histogram",
      "frequency-density"
    ],
    "tier": "extended"
  }
]
